# Immutable factories & iterating

## `List.of` / `Set.of` / `Map.of` (Java 9)

- Return **structurally immutable** collections
- Thread-safe to share; no defensive copies

```java
List.of("admin", "editor");            // add() -> UnsupportedOperationException
Map.ofEntries(Map.entry("a", 1), ...); // past the 10-entry limit
```

## Iterating

- **enhanced `for`** for any `Iterable` — preferred
- `Iterator.remove()` to delete mid-walk; else `ConcurrentModificationException`
